This is a full-featured music player which is very easy to use.    I especially like the ability to ignore folders, such as MP3 files which are ringtones or voice recordings.  You can create playlists, or you can just select certain tracks and use the "play selected" function.  You can even drag songs to a different order in the playing queue.  The music lists can be refreshed to reflect additions/deletions in the actual music folders, and empty folders are not shown.  I also like that it does not try to deal with cloud storage or update metadata from the Internet.  One bug I found is that Genres are not refreshed.  If you edit the metadata on a PC, for example, then delete all the folders in PowerAudio Pro and they copy the edited tracks to the phone again, Genres which were detected on the first read and now no longer exist in any track are not deleted.  Clicking on one of these "phantom" Genres shows no tracks, of course.  It seems the Genre view "refresh" circle should update this list and delete empty Genres.  The second bug is that, if a MP3 track is played from My Files, PowerAudio Pro resumes a playing queue instead of playing the single track and returning to My Files.
